LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 750
Introduced by Spivey, 13.
Read first time January 07, 2026
Committee: Appropriations
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Health Care Facility Licensure Act; to
2 amend section 71-401, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024;
3 to state legislative intent relating to reimbursement for PACE
4 program services; and to repeal the original section.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB750 LB750
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 71-401, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 71-401 Sections 71-401 to 71-479 and section 2 of this act shall be
4 known and may be cited as the Health Care Facility Licensure Act.
5 Sec. 2. It is the intent of the Legislature to direct the
6 Department of Health and Human Services to increase the reimbursement
7 rate for PACE program services to no less than eighty percent of the cost
8 of care received at a PACE center.
9 Sec. 3. Original section 71-401, Revised Statutes Cumulative
10 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
